.TH RECT 1
.SH NAME
rect \- delete/replace a rectangular area of text in an acme window
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rect
[
.I replacement
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Rect
deletes a rectangular area of text in an acme window.
If
.I replacement
is given, it replaces each line in
the rectangle with the
.IR replacement .
The input rectangular area is specified by making
a selection in the acme window.  The beginning and
end of the selection define the top left and
bottom right corners of the rectangle.
.PP
.I Rect
is useful when dealing with text in multi-column
formats (e.g., log files).  It can also be used to
comment/uncomment, indent/unindent source code.
.SH SOURCE
.B /appl/acme/acme/bin/rect.b
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR acme (1)
